    <name>
				<text>6.2.3.3 Compute sech given tanh</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise&nbsp;</p>
<p>Given \(\tanh{@arg@} = {@tanh@} \). Compute \( \rm{sech}\) \( {@arg@} \). Round up and enter 4 decimal places. If the answer has less than 4 decimal places, then enter zero(s) at the end.</p> 
<p>\( \rm{sech} \) \({@arg@} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Use the identity \( \rm{sech}^2\)\({@arg@} = 1 - \tanh^2{@arg@}\) to calculate \(\rm{sech}^2\)\({@arg@}\), then take the (positive) square root to obtain \(\rm{sech}\) \({@arg@} \), noting that \(\rm{sech}\) \( {@arg@} = \frac{1}{\cosh{@arg@}} &gt;0\) for all values of \({@arg@}\).</p>
<p>\(\rm{sech}\) \({@arg@} = \sqrt{1 - \tanh^2{@arg@}} = \sqrt{1 - ({@tanh@})^2} ={@ta@}\) to four significant figures (or four decimal places in this case).</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
